1
00:01:31,020 --> 00:01:34,979
[The Lost National Treasure]

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,810
[Episode 20]

3
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:26,700
Wen Wen.

4
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:27,680
Mu.

5
00:02:29,150 --> 00:02:30,810
Where's your sister-in-law?

6
00:02:33,970 --> 00:02:34,550
Give it to me.

7
00:02:34,550 --> 00:02:34,960
Okay.

8
00:02:52,870 --> 00:02:53,329
Wen Wen,

9
00:02:53,910 --> 00:02:56,310
plug in the electric heater
I just brought.

10
00:02:58,800 --> 00:02:59,660
I don't want it.

11
00:03:00,150 --> 00:03:00,880
Take it away.

12
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:12,080
Shulan,

13
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:14,910
the mountain is full of negative energy.

14
00:03:14,910 --> 00:03:16,280
It's not good for your health.

15
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,079
Let's go home.

16
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:21,020
No matter how heavy
the negative energy is here,

17
00:03:21,110 --> 00:03:24,310
it's not as heavy
as the negative energy surrounding you.

18
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:27,470
The cold will aggravate your rheumatism.

19
00:03:27,470 --> 00:03:28,800
You can be angry with me,

20
00:03:29,150 --> 00:03:31,010
but don't mistreat your own body.

21
00:03:31,470 --> 00:03:33,930
No amount of suffering
can atone for my sins.

22
00:03:34,960 --> 00:03:36,560
It won't bring my child back.

23
00:03:43,190 --> 00:03:44,390
The sin is mine alone.

24
00:03:45,030 --> 00:03:47,280
If anyone should suffer, it should be me.

25
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:48,079
Rest assured,

26
00:03:48,680 --> 00:03:50,880
from now on, I'll bear the burden alone.

27
00:03:52,190 --> 00:03:54,450
I won't touch any dirty stuff ever again.

28
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,480
Shusheng won't touch it either.

29
00:03:58,360 --> 00:03:59,160
Alright then.

30
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:01,190
So stay here,

31
00:04:02,310 --> 00:04:05,040
and copy scriptures
with me to atone for our sins.

32
00:04:58,300 --> 00:05:00,480
Brother, it's not worth it
for such a small matter.

33
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:01,880
Here's the stuff for you.

34
00:06:09,740 --> 00:06:12,670
When the big river runs dry,
the small river dries up.

35
00:06:12,670 --> 00:06:15,470
Uncle will be the big river
of Qinchuan from now on.

36
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:19,930
Where did you get so much money?

37
00:06:20,460 --> 00:06:21,320
I saved it up.

38
00:06:54,510 --> 00:06:55,370
Who is Luo Qing?

39
00:06:55,430 --> 00:06:58,270
She's a cultural relic expert
from the provincial institute.

40
00:06:58,270 --> 00:06:59,000
I'll pick up.

41
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:00,410
Captain Qi,

42
00:07:01,860 --> 00:07:02,720
Ms. Luo Qing,

43
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,210
what's the matter?

44
00:07:04,210 --> 00:07:05,480
That empty tomb has been excavated.

45
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:06,600
There's another tomb underneath.

46
00:07:06,600 --> 00:07:08,430
That's great!

47
00:07:08,430 --> 00:07:09,800
Why are you so jumpy?

48
00:07:10,690 --> 00:07:12,620
It's nothing. I'll be right there.

49
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,980
You're coming with me to the site.

50
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:18,020
What about picking up the kid?

51
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:19,190
Call Mom.

52
00:07:19,870 --> 00:07:20,750
You must go.

53
00:07:21,190 --> 00:07:22,050
Let me tell you,

54
00:07:22,170 --> 00:07:24,500
I'll show you what I do every day.

55
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:00,680
Director Zhang.

56
00:08:02,270 --> 00:08:02,830
Captain Qi.

57
00:08:02,830 --> 00:08:04,270
Professor Xiang, you're here too.

58
00:08:04,270 --> 00:08:06,600
-Yes, I'm here. Captain Qi.
-You're here.

59
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:07,660
And who is this?

60
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:08,800
I'm his wife.

61
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:10,250
How is it?

62
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:12,810
I heard there's another tomb underneath.

63
00:08:12,950 --> 00:08:15,280
Come, come, have a seat.
Let's talk about it.

64
00:08:15,280 --> 00:08:16,230
Please, sit down.

65
00:08:16,230 --> 00:08:18,160
Yes, they're still digging below.

66
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:20,760
Any new discoveries?

67
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:23,160
Nothing yet.

68
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:24,720
We're waiting for news.

69
00:08:25,430 --> 00:08:26,360
There's hope.

70
00:08:29,190 --> 00:08:29,560
Good.

71
00:08:30,190 --> 00:08:30,600
You...

72
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,260
Captain Qi.

73
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:33,750
Ms. Luo Qing, how is it?

74
00:08:34,549 --> 00:08:35,840
It's still an empty tomb.

75
00:08:35,840 --> 00:08:36,600
-Empty?
-What?

76
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:38,000
There are no burial objects below,

77
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:40,390
no funerary objects,
coffins, or skeletal remains.

78
00:08:40,390 --> 00:08:41,480
There's nothing at all.

79
00:08:41,480 --> 00:08:43,539
It's the same as the first empty tomb.

80
00:08:44,480 --> 00:08:46,480
The tomb owner must have been crazy.

81
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:49,080
Why dig two deep empty tombs?

82
00:08:51,030 --> 00:08:52,390
I have a bold guess.

83
00:08:53,210 --> 00:08:54,720
No one would go to such lengths

84
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:56,000
to design

85
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:58,030
two such deep empty tombs for no reason.

86
00:08:58,030 --> 00:08:59,600
There's only one possibility.

87
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:00,860
It's to prevent theft.

88
00:09:01,630 --> 00:09:03,410
So I think the real burial chamber

89
00:09:03,410 --> 00:09:05,270
should be at an even deeper level.

90
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:07,400
A third layer?

91
00:09:08,670 --> 00:09:10,870
Someone with such intricate planning,

92
00:09:11,080 --> 00:09:13,210
according to the Lv family genealogy,

93
00:09:13,240 --> 00:09:14,840
there can only be one person.

94
00:09:16,030 --> 00:09:17,920
Our ancestor, Lv Dalin.

95
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:23,200
Director Zhang,

96
00:09:23,790 --> 00:09:24,790
what do you think?

97
00:09:32,790 --> 00:09:33,720
It's hard to say.

98
00:09:35,550 --> 00:09:37,120
It's not impossible.

99
00:09:38,670 --> 00:09:41,480
We still need facts and evidence
to speak for themselves.

100
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:42,870
Just keep digging.

101
00:09:42,890 --> 00:09:44,820
You'll have evidence once you dig.

102
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:47,270
Always saying "it's hard to say," come on.

103
00:09:47,270 --> 00:09:49,910
If we dig further,
we'll hit the Liaojiang stone layer.

104
00:09:49,910 --> 00:09:51,440
What's the Liaojiang stone layer?

105
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:53,150
It's a type of grayish-white rock.

106
00:09:53,150 --> 00:09:54,350
It's extremely hard.

107
00:09:54,440 --> 00:09:54,910
Yes,

108
00:09:55,440 --> 00:09:57,400
when local people dig wells,

109
00:09:57,670 --> 00:09:58,850
if they encounter this kind of stone,

110
00:09:58,850 --> 00:10:00,380
they can't dig any further.

111
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:03,240
Even if it's hard, we still have to dig.

112
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:04,370
What's the big deal?

113
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:06,020
Captain Qi.

114
00:10:06,550 --> 00:10:08,320
We're different from you.

115
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:10,200
You handle cases,

116
00:10:10,630 --> 00:10:13,670
taking one step forward
with two legs following closely behind.

117
00:10:13,670 --> 00:10:15,670
for us, whether we can take that step

118
00:10:16,550 --> 00:10:18,750
depends on passing three checkpoints.

119
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,300
Don't be in a hurry.

120
00:10:20,670 --> 00:10:22,750
We'll let you know
once we've finished our research.

121
00:10:22,750 --> 00:10:23,870
It's not that I'm impatient,

122
00:10:23,870 --> 00:10:25,470
it's that the case is urgent.

123
00:10:26,370 --> 00:10:27,720
Just dig!

124
00:10:33,910 --> 00:10:35,120
You can pass
six checkpoints for all I care.

125
00:10:35,120 --> 00:10:37,550
Aren't you going to
dig anyway after all that research?

126
00:10:37,550 --> 00:10:38,550
Shut up, will you?

127
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:42,000
You're so indecisive.

128
00:10:42,030 --> 00:10:42,960
Fine, I'll wait, I'll wait.

129
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:43,560
I'm sorry.

130
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:47,320
What are you doing all day long?

131
00:10:51,510 --> 00:10:52,150
Ms. Luo.

132
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:53,200
Ms. Luo.

133
00:10:53,550 --> 00:10:55,550
There's a major discovery in pit M1.

134
00:11:02,440 --> 00:11:03,120
Your leg

135
00:11:04,010 --> 00:11:06,410
doesn't seem to
be getting any better here.

136
00:11:06,670 --> 00:11:07,480
If you ask me,

137
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:10,320
we should go back down the mountain.

138
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:29,340
Your phone is ringing.

139
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:31,400
Don't worry about it.

140
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:46,480
Hello?

141
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:50,040
I understand.

142
00:11:50,550 --> 00:11:52,010
I'll come down right away.

143
00:12:07,840 --> 00:12:08,440
Sir,

144
00:12:08,870 --> 00:12:10,470
how about a fortune telling?

145
00:12:12,040 --> 00:12:12,790
You don't even know

146
00:12:12,790 --> 00:12:14,600
where your next meal is coming from,

147
00:12:14,600 --> 00:12:16,000
yet you're telling fortunes for others?

148
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,930
My next meal is right here with you.

149
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:20,890
I see that your brows are radiant,

150
00:12:20,910 --> 00:12:22,200
your forehead is full and moist,

151
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,360
surely a sign of
great fortune in your future.

152
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:27,630
However, there's a slight unfavorable
aura around your eyes,

153
00:12:27,630 --> 00:12:29,080
spreading to your forehead,

154
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:31,610
which might affect
your children's fortune.

155
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:37,790
So, do you see

156
00:12:38,510 --> 00:12:40,040
any offspring in my future?

157
00:12:40,150 --> 00:12:40,480
Yes,

158
00:12:45,080 --> 00:12:46,030
within a year.

159
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,060
That's enough.

160
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,860
You're having a hard time too.

161
00:12:57,550 --> 00:12:59,280
You got one thing right though.

162
00:12:59,630 --> 00:13:01,480
Your next meal is indeed with me.

163
00:13:02,150 --> 00:13:02,840
Go eat.

164
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:06,140
Look at this.

165
00:13:06,550 --> 00:13:09,670
His name was Daya, courtesy name Zhengzhi,

166
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:11,840
the youngest son of the Lord.

167
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:15,510
This indicates that
the occupant of tomb M1

168
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:17,320
is Lv Daya.

169
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:18,870
The Lord?

170
00:13:19,670 --> 00:13:21,470
It refers to his father, Lv Ying.

171
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:23,910
There's another passage here.

172
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:24,910
Look at this part.

173
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:27,440
Tong had two sons, the eldest named Ying,

174
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:29,450
who held the position of
Assistant Director of the Palace Library,

175
00:13:29,450 --> 00:13:33,030
and was posthumously awarded
the title of Senior Court Gentleman.

176
00:13:33,030 --> 00:13:35,290
So this tomb's occupant is Lv Ying's son,

177
00:13:35,840 --> 00:13:36,440
and Lv Ying

178
00:13:37,030 --> 00:13:38,830
is also the eldest son of Lv Tong.

179
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:41,320
Lv Daya's second son

180
00:13:41,750 --> 00:13:43,610
was adopted by one of his cousins.

181
00:13:44,320 --> 00:13:45,320
Can you guess who?

182
00:13:46,510 --> 00:13:49,320
Could it be our founding father, Lv Dalin?

183
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:50,550
That's right, it's Lv Dalin.

184
00:13:50,550 --> 00:13:52,630
Because Lv Dalin
had no children of his own,

185
00:13:52,630 --> 00:13:53,870
so the child was adopted by him.

186
00:13:53,870 --> 00:13:55,120
There's another interesting point.

187
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:56,320
Come and look at this.

188
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:57,700
Here, let me take over.

189
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:00,960
Take a look at this tomb epitaph cover.

190
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:03,690
See if you notice
anything different on the back.

191
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:06,640
There are words on it.

192
00:14:10,720 --> 00:14:13,320
It says "Epitaph of Lord Zhang,
Former Prefect

193
00:14:13,790 --> 00:14:16,790
of Dingzhou
of the Great Tang, Upper Pillar of State."

194
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:18,960
You're right. This tomb cover

195
00:14:19,270 --> 00:14:20,360
was repurposed.

196
00:14:20,910 --> 00:14:22,120
It originally belonged to

197
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:24,030
a Tang Dynasty governor surnamed Zhang.

198
00:14:24,030 --> 00:14:25,600
So during the Song Dynasty,

199
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:27,720
this tomb cover was already an antique.

200
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:28,630
And in the Lv family,

201
00:14:28,630 --> 00:14:31,690
wasn't Lv Dalin the one
who loved collecting antiques?

202
00:14:32,030 --> 00:14:32,890
Think about it.

203
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:36,360
Lv Dalin's stepson was Lv Daya's son.

204
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:39,100
And Lv Dalin loved collecting antiques.

205
00:14:39,390 --> 00:14:40,150
This tomb cover

206
00:14:40,150 --> 00:14:42,000
was likely one of Lv Dalin's collections

207
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:44,660
that was eventually
used for Lv Daya's funeral.

208
00:14:44,790 --> 00:14:46,720
M2 and M1 are so close to each other.

209
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,270
The more we talk about it,

210
00:14:48,270 --> 00:14:50,670
the more it seems
that M2 is Lv Dalin's tomb.

211
00:14:57,870 --> 00:14:58,890
The excavation of M1

212
00:14:58,890 --> 00:15:00,390
has to some extent helped

213
00:15:00,390 --> 00:15:02,390
confirm the identity of M2's occupant.

214
00:15:02,390 --> 00:15:03,440
Now we believe

215
00:15:03,510 --> 00:15:05,910
that M2 is very likely
to be Lv Dalin's tomb.

216
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:08,840
This is a newly discovered tomb cover

217
00:15:09,150 --> 00:15:10,790
that has been repurposed.

218
00:15:10,870 --> 00:15:12,800
It has inscriptions on both sides.

219
00:15:12,840 --> 00:15:15,870
The front side is inscribed with "Tomb of
Mr. Lv, Retired Officer of Song Dynasty,"

220
00:15:15,870 --> 00:15:17,800
which refers to the occupant of M1.

221
00:15:19,550 --> 00:15:22,120
The back side reads
"Epitaph of Lord Zhang,
Former Prefect

222
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:24,440
of Dingzhou
of the Great Tang, Upper Pillar of State."

223
00:15:24,440 --> 00:15:26,300
The exact identity is uncertain.

224
00:15:28,630 --> 00:15:29,290
Chief Wang,

225
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:31,270
if we dig deeper,

226
00:15:31,600 --> 00:15:34,000
we'll encounter the Liaojiang stone layer.

227
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,360
If we're too gentle,
we can't dig through it.

228
00:15:35,360 --> 00:15:37,690
If we're too forceful, it might collapse.

229
00:15:38,200 --> 00:15:39,400
From what we know now,

230
00:15:39,550 --> 00:15:41,390
both the first and second tomb layers

231
00:15:41,390 --> 00:15:42,990
have a lot of collapsed soil.

232
00:15:43,750 --> 00:15:45,670
If the third layer is a real tomb

233
00:15:46,670 --> 00:15:48,000
and hasn't been looted,

234
00:15:48,750 --> 00:15:50,240
it could easily collapse,

235
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:52,120
which would cause

236
00:15:52,390 --> 00:15:53,840
irreversible damage.

237
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:55,500
Your concerns are valid.

238
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:59,420
The Lv Family Tomb
is now attracting a lot of attention.

239
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:01,450
If it's really Lv Dalin's tomb,

240
00:16:02,240 --> 00:16:04,440
then millions of eyes will be watching.

241
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:06,770
I suggest

242
00:16:07,030 --> 00:16:09,790
we proceed with caution
in further excavating M2.

243
00:16:09,790 --> 00:16:12,680
We should first develop
a plan before considering excavation.

244
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:13,390
We need to base our work on

245
00:16:13,390 --> 00:16:16,320
legal, standardized,
and technological criteria.

246
00:16:16,550 --> 00:16:17,960
We must ensure everything is foolproof.

247
00:16:17,960 --> 00:16:19,480
We will come up with

248
00:16:19,670 --> 00:16:22,330
the safest excavation
plan as soon as possible.

249
00:16:26,590 --> 00:16:27,150
Mr. Mu,

250
00:16:27,910 --> 00:16:29,040
you're impressive.

251
00:16:30,550 --> 00:16:31,840
You have a keen eye.

252
00:16:32,430 --> 00:16:35,490
You've acquired so many
good items in such a short time.

253
00:16:35,630 --> 00:16:37,870
Your ability to take action is remarkable.

254
00:16:37,870 --> 00:16:39,270
Mr. Zhao, you flatter me.

255
00:16:39,600 --> 00:16:41,130
I owe it all to your support.

256
00:16:41,560 --> 00:16:43,160
It's all thanks to your care.

257
00:16:43,270 --> 00:16:45,530
I've just been riding on your coattails.

258
00:16:46,010 --> 00:16:48,270
What coattails of mine are you riding on?

259
00:16:48,790 --> 00:16:49,910
Speaking of it,

260
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,150
recently,

261
00:16:52,150 --> 00:16:53,880
I've indeed heard some things.

262
00:16:54,600 --> 00:16:56,060
They say in Qinchuan city,

263
00:16:56,440 --> 00:16:58,750
there's someone called Uncle

264
00:17:00,840 --> 00:17:03,360
who's been making quite a stir.

265
00:17:03,920 --> 00:17:05,880
Some things have reached my ears.

266
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:09,240
Mr. Mu,

267
00:17:10,030 --> 00:17:10,880
in life,

268
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:13,109
one should

269
00:17:13,970 --> 00:17:15,030
keep a low profile.

270
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:17,300
A tall tree catches the wind.

271
00:17:17,300 --> 00:17:17,900
Is that so?

272
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:19,030
Right.

273
00:17:19,359 --> 00:17:20,359
You are right.

274
00:17:23,750 --> 00:17:24,280
Mr. Zhao.

275
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:26,240
They're here.

